<p>
<h1>Get an analytics report on all API traffic</h1> 
</p>

<div class="row">
	<div class="span6" style="width:340px;"><p>
		<b>API Platform Base Path:</b>
		<p>https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1/o/{org_name}</p>
		<b>API Resource Path:</b>
		<p>/environments/{environment_name}/stats</p>
		<p>
		Retrieve the metrics for all the available APIs for a given customer in a specific organization and environment.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="span6" style="width:340px;">
		<p>
		<b>Verb:</b>
		<span class="verb-GET">GET</span>
		</p>
		<b>Auth:</b>
		Basic Auth
		</p>


		<p>
		<b><a href="http://apigee.com/docs/api/content/reporting-api-analytics">Developer Guide Topic</a></b>
		</p>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="span18">
	<p>
	Use the GET method to retrieve the metrics for all the available APIs for a given customer in a specific organization and environment. All API traffic displays the total daily throughput over the last 3 months for all APIs in the account.
	</p>



<b>Sample Response:</b> 
	<pre>{
    "environments": [
       {
           "metrics": [
               {
                   "name": "message_count",
                   "values": [
                          {
                           "timestamp": 1335241800000,
                           "value": "9090.0"
                          }
                   ]
               }
           ],
           "name": "test"
       }
    ],
    "metaData": {}
}
}</pre>




</div>


            </div>
